description: Net Zero Renewable Energy Inc. designs, develops, manufactures, assembles, and distributes structural building systems in Canada. The company provides modular building/home systems with integrated hybrid alternative energy systems. It offers fiberglass reinforced structural insulted panels, ultra-light solar panels, controlled environment growing pods, and alternative energy producing mobile trailers under the ENERTEC brand. The company also provides PWR wagon, a stock trailer customized to offer a remote site power source through its self-contained solar energy system. The company was formerly known as EnerDynamic Hybrid Technologies Corp. and is based in Net Zero Renewable Energy Inc. in January 2022. Net Zero Renewable Energy Inc. is headquartered in Niagara Falls, Canada.
